locality: Eleven reef sites selected inside the Ha Long Natural World Heritage bounary
samplingProtocol: Fish abundance was assessed using the underwater fish visual census technique. After locating the transect site by GPS, a 50 m transect line was laid parallel to the shore. A SCUBA diver swam along transect at a constat speed for 30 minutes. All fish visible within 5 m width were identified to the lowest possible taxon on both sides of transect and 5 m above.
